{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":35097,"name":"evol","username":"evolgames","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/evolgames/{size}/3169_2.png","created_at":"2020-01-25T20:49:42.839Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello, I‚Äôm using the 2dConstraints sample. I want to make objects without image sprites, just filling the 2d primitives with specific colors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI don‚Äôt see how I can set the color of the sprite. I noticed it‚Äôs drawing the outline of the polygon with the Debug renderer, which is fine, but I have no idea how I can modify that debug fill color. I tried doing the following:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e    for v=1,vn do\n    verts[v]=guys[1].shape:GetVertex(v)\n    end\n   --debugRend:AddPolygon(Vector3(1.2, -0.3,0), Vector3(2.5, -0.8,0), Vector3(2.8, -0.3,0), Vector3(2.8, 0.5,0),Color(1,0,0), false)\n   \n   local pos=guys[1].body:GetPosition()\n   debugRend:AddPolygon(Vector3(verts[1]+pos),Vector3(verts[2]+pos),Vector3(verts[3]+pos),Vector3(verts[4]+pos),Color(1,1,1), false)\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBecause I just want to draw a polygon where these 2d rigid bodies are. But there is no function to find the position of the 2d rigid body. At least not that I can find‚Ä¶\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAdding a polygon to the debug renderer lets me choose the color but then  I can‚Äôt get the position of the body to draw. And for the 2d rigid bodies it appears they can only be drawn with image sprites?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnyone know how I can just fill a 2d rigidbody with a color?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-01-26T16:29:27.104Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":25,"readers_count":24,"score":35.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":5842,"topic_slug":"how-to-fill-a-2d-shape","display_username":"evol","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null